Study Questions for Lab 1, ECE 152
Marshal Horn

1.
a. A tool chain is a group of executables used to compile for a specific device.
b. Software testing is the process of verifying the functionality of your program and determining what is neccessary to fix bugs.
c. Hardware testing is the process of making sure the device you're programming works how you think it does.
d. A makefile gives directions to the compiler for how to compile your program.
e. An environmental variable is a dynamic variable that affects how your program operates.  In BASH, an example of this is $PATH.

2.
It seems this course will move more slowly than last term.  I expect to learn about interrupts and communication protocols, implementing and troubleshooting both.  I expect to spend about 5 - 10 hours a week on it.